history.content:
Check out cvc.edu
Search common classes that fullfill h/as requirements, or IGETC requirements. For example, there are a few course equivalencies to sociology 3ac if you search the site.

Community college coursework is considered all lower-division since they are a 2 year institution. You would have to take the course at a 4 year institution. If you are EECS, please contact your ESS Advisor for the evaluation process.

I'm looking for online upper-div H/SS courses to take to complete EECS requirements, and Physics 7B also. How do I find which community college's which online summer classes satisfy Berkeley requirements?

I tried Assist.org but it only tells the agreements between universities after knowing the college. I don't even know if the college has those transferable courses available in the summer, I have to go individually to figure out that website to find the info I need.

Is there an easy way to see which courses satisfy Berkeley engineering H/SS requirements?

Is there an easy way to see which community colleges have those online courses?

Thanks
history.subject: Online H/SS: how to find CC courses that satisfy?
